INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (753,1,'2024-03-22 16:00:10','2024-03-22 13:00:10','<p class=\"p1\">Privacy Notice for Website Visitors in accordance with the Personal Data Protection Law No. 6698</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">As Solino Solar Energy Systems Engineering Import Export and Construction Industry and Trade Inc. (‚ÄúSolino‚Äù or ‚ÄúCompany‚Äù), we prioritize the security of your personal data processed by us as the data controller on our website http://solino.local/ in accordance with the Personal Data Protection Law (‚ÄúPDPL‚Äù or ‚ÄúLaw‚Äù), and therefore, we aim to enlighten you within the scope of this Privacy Notice through the explanations we will make in this Privacy Notice.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Your personal data;</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">‚Ä¢ Will be processed within the framework of the purpose requiring processing and limited and proportionate to this purpose,</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">‚Ä¢ By preserving the accuracy and most up-to-date status of personal data as you have notified us or as it has been notified,</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">‚Ä¢ Will be recorded, stored, preserved, reorganized, shared with the competent institutions authorized to request these personal data under the law, and transferred to third parties, classified and processed in other ways listed in the PDPL.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">DEFINITIONS</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Personal Data: Any information relating to an identified or identifiable real person.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Data Controller: It refers to the real or legal person who determines the purposes and means of processing personal data and is responsible for establishing and managing the data recording system.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Law No. 6698: Personal Data Protection Law No. 6698</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Supplier: It refers to the real or legal person from whom goods or services are purchased.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Business Partner: It refers to the real or legal persons with whom we provide partnership within the framework of a contract for the performance of a specific job in the context of our business activities, economically and legally independent.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">PROCESSED PERSONAL DATA</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">The following personal data provided by visitors may be processed by the Company: Identity Data: Name, surname. Contact Data: Email address, phone number, city information Transaction Security Data: IP address, Device IMEI Number, Device MAC Address, Traffic (Connection time/duration, Communication Quantity etc.), cookie information.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">PURPOSES OF PROCESSING YOUR PERSONAL DATA</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Your personal data are processed by the Company in accordance with the Law and other secondary regulations and Institution decisions attached to the Law, within the framework of the purposes and legal reasons stated below:</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">‚Ä¢ Communication: We may contact you for various purposes using the personal data you provide through http://solino.local/. Sending reminder and alert messages and responding to messages you have sent to us are examples of these. Corporate communication is also aimed.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">‚Ä¢ Legal Obligations: Your personal data can be processed, transferred and kept within the scope of any legislation to which http://solino.local/ is subject, and for the period stipulated in the relevant legislation or necessary for the purpose.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">‚Ä¢ Dispute Resolution: Solino may process your personal data to prove that it has carried out lawful transactions and fulfilled its legal obligations and to ensure the resolution of disputes in the future, and share it with relevant legal authorities.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">‚Ä¢ Improvement of Services and Customer Satisfaction: Your personal data are processed for the purpose of improving your experience on http://solino.local/, conducting analytical studies to improve customer satisfaction and service quality by evaluating your requests, complaints and suggestions.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">LEGAL GROUNDS FOR PROCESSING YOUR PERSONAL DATA</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Your personal data are processed on http://solino.local/ if at least one of the legal grounds specified in the Law exists. The legal grounds on which the above-mentioned personal data processing purposes are based are as follows:</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">‚Ä¢ Communication transactions and related actions are carried out based on the legal reason of establishing or performing a contract specified in Article 5/2(c) of the Law.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">‚Ä¢ Data processing activities carried out to fulfill our legal obligations are based on the legal reason explicitly specified in Article 5/2 (√ß) of the Law.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">‚Ä¢ Cases where personal data are processed for the resolution of disputes are based on the legal reason stated in Article 5/2(e) of the Law, which is the establishment, exercise or protection of a right.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">‚Ä¢ Activities based on the purposes of improving services and customer satisfaction and communication purposes are carried out based on the legitimate interest legal reason specified in Article 5/2(f) of the Law.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">METHODS OF COLLECTING YOUR PERSONAL DATA</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">In the context of the services provided by Solino and the above-mentioned data processing purposes, your personal data can be collected electronically, via e-mail channels, through http://solino.local/ by using all kinds of data entry opportunities, communication and other forms, and through relevant analysis tools. In addition, your personal data are obtained through cookies used on http://solino.local/.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">TRANSFER OF YOUR PERSONAL DATA</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Your personal data may be shared with relevant institutions and organizations for the completion of transactions made through http://solino.local/, the fulfillment of legal obligations, evaluation and management by Solino and for the purposes of managing Solino and as requested within the scope of the legal obligations. In addition, your personal data may be shared with Solino\'s business partners, affiliated companies, and relevant public institutions and organizations within the framework of the conditions specified in Articles 8 and 9 of the Law and for the fulfillment of legal obligations.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">SECURITY OF YOUR PERSONAL DATA</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Solino takes reasonable measures to ensure the security of personal data, prevent unlawful processing, and prevent unauthorized access risks, accidental loss of data, intentional deletion of data, or damage to data. Necessary technical and physical measures are taken to prevent access to personal data by persons other than those authorized to access it. In this context, in particular, the authorization system is designed so that no one can access more personal data than necessary. Solino conducts and ensures the necessary audits to ensure compliance with the provisions of Law No. 6698 and other relevant legislation.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">YOUR RIGHTS</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">As personal data owners, if you submit your requests regarding your rights to the Company, the Company will conclude your requests within the shortest time possible and within thirty (30) days at the latest, free of charge, depending on the nature of the request. However, if the transaction requires an additional cost, the fee specified in the tariff determined by the Personal Data Protection Board will be charged by the Company. In this context:</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">‚Ä¢ Learning whether personal data is processed,</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">‚Ä¢ Requesting information if personal data has been processed,</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">‚Ä¢ Learning the purpose of processing personal data and whether they are used appropriately for their purpose,</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">‚Ä¢ Knowing the third parties to whom personal data are transferred at home or abroad,</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">‚Ä¢ Requesting the correction of personal data in case of incomplete or incorrect processing and, within this scope, requesting the notification of the transactions made to third parties to whom personal data have been transferred,</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">‚Ä¢ Requesting the deletion or destruction of personal data in case the reasons requiring their processing disappear despite being processed in accordance with the Law and other relevant provisions, and requesting that the transactions made within this scope be notified to third parties to whom personal data have been transferred,</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">‚Ä¢ Objecting to the emergence of a result against the person by analyzing the processed data solely through automated systems,</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">‚Ä¢ Requesting the compensation of damages in case of damage due to the unlawful processing of personal data, you have rights. In matters concerning the processing of personal data, you must submit your request to the Company by filling out the application form on the Company\'s website, in writing, or by using the registered electronic mail (KEP) address, secure electronic signature, mobile signature, or the electronic mail address previously notified to us and recorded in our records.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"></p>','Clarification Text','','inherit','closed','closed','','729-revision-v1','','','2024-03-22 16:00:10','2024-03-22 13:00:10','',729,'http://solino.local/?p=753',0,'revision','',0);
